'''Carl J. Hudecek''' (born December 3, 1934) is an American, internationally known expert on [[glass-to-metal seal|sealing glasses]],<ref>{{cite news |title=Techneglas maintains cutting edge in glass technology |url=http://findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_qa5333/is_199811/ai_n21433307/ |work=Toledo Business Journal |date=November 1, 1998 |accessdate=July 31, 2009 }}</ref> [[expansion joint|metal expansion and contraction]], and [[oxidation state|metal oxidation]] processes for glass sealing. Hudecek holds or co-holds many U.S. and international patents in sealing glasses, television picture [[vacuum tube|tube]] materials and processing, and sealing [[alloy]]s.
Hudecek was born in [[Toledo, Ohio]].{{citation needed|date=October 2014}} He is from [[Perrysburg, Ohio]] and graduated from the [[University of Toledo]].<ref name=ACBL>{{cite book |author=[[American Contract Bridge League]]|title=The Official Encyclopedia of Bridge (5th Edition)|page=651}}</ref>
Most of his working career was spent at [[Owens-Illinois]] Glass Company in Toledo, where he was chief physicist and laboratory manager. Hudecek was one of the U.S. pioneers in designing and installing [[turnkey]] [[manufacturing operations]] for sealing glasses in Russia and Germany. Through his consulting company, [[Perrysburg, Ohio|Perrysburg]], Ohio-based Bridgecon Services, Hudecek consults in the area of sealing glasses. He has also taught courses on sealing and joining at [[Rutgers University]] and [[Missouri University of Science and Technology|Missouri School of Mines]].
In addition, Hudecek is an expert at the game of [[contract bridge]]. He won the national [[American Contract Bridge League]] [[Nail Life Master Open Pairs|Life Master Open Pairs]] championship in 1966, partnered by Ray Zoller.<ref>{{cite news |title=Bridge:; Ohio Partnership Wins Life Master Men's Pairs |url=https://www.nytimes.com/1966/11/24/archives/bridge-ohio-partnership-wins-life-master-mens-pairs.html |work=[[The New York Times]] |date=November 24, 1966 |accessdate=July 31, 2009 | first=Alan | last=Truscott}}</ref> Hudecek has been a member of the panel of experts for ''[[The Bridge World]]'' magazine for more than 45 years and has written many bridge articles and commentaries.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bridgeworld.com/default.asp?d%3Dtbw_extra%26f%3Darchive_edition008.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2013-09-02 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071019001632/http://www.bridgeworld.com/default.asp?d=tbw_extra&f=archive_edition008.html |archivedate=2007-10-19 |df= }}{{full citation needed|date=May 2014}}<!--served as file archive_edition008.html but appears to be current; e.g. the current bidding contest--></ref>{{citation needed|date=May 2014}}
